14/01/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan expressed optimism Tuesday (13 January) about prospects for launching EU accession negotiations by the end of this year. 
In a speech to the ruling Justice and Development party, he noted that relations with Turkey's neighbours and other countries have improved noticeably over the last year, a significant step on the road to EU integration.
In other news Tuesday, Turkey and Finland signed an agreement on co-operation in preventing and fighting crimes, including drug and human trafficking, and money laundering. 
Ankara has already signed bilateral co-operation agreements with 43 countries. 
(Milliyet - 14/01/04; Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 13/01/04)
